            <p facs="#facs_75_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>- H62-
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>in which the naturalancetance of theseütories and symbol is shaken by.criticism, you produce a
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>revolt. You produce a negative revolt which then condes those long periods, perhaps for lifetime,
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>in which the child which has been introduced into these symbol is thrown out of these symbols
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>because it asked questions, and these questions areontical questions.
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>For this reason, especially my generation, many parents hesitated, completely, and finally
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_75_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>restricted themselves completely from this act of introduced the children into the reality of a
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>;iligious community, its symbol's and its life. But if this WAS done, then an "empty specé,
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>a vacuum, was created, and it was very questionable, as history has shown, whether this vacuum
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>could be filled later on at all, or whether it remained a vacuum because of forms of resistance connected
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>with the whole rebellious attitude of all younger deserations against the older ones. So we stand before
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>the great problem of giving contents, which later on must be or actually will be shaken, and often
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>radically shaken, by the lnavidable criticism coming from the humanistic side, in theatger sense
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>of that word; on the other hand, the danger of producing a vacuum which remains a vacuum for a
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>certain time, and then might be filled by symbol of a lower or evenbringing character, as it happened
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>in Europe.
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>What is the task given by this alternative? Now my answer would be—but this is a
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_75_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/> July theoretical answer, not in the sense that it is true in theory but wrong in practice--this is
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>nonsense; whoever says that has never thought about these two words—but the truth in
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>theory demands a tremendous toil and thinking and work and experimenting in practice.
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>Nevertheless it remains truth.
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>de
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>Cela nʼentraîne
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_10" n="N010"/>lʼhonneur de lʼautre
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_11" n="N011"/>de mon ami
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_12" n="N012"/>de Vous
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_13" n="N013"/>de vous.
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_14" n="N014"/>dʼune manière est devenu avec vous
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_15" n="N015"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_75_tr_2_tl_16" n="N016"/>dʼauteur de vous
            </p>
            
